**First-Price Sealed-Bid Auction Equilibrium.** Two bidders, $V_{i}\stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim}\mathrm{Uniform}[0,1]$. Higher bidder wins and pays their own bid. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item Show the symmetric BNE strategy is $b^{*}(v)=v/2$.

\item What is each bidder's expected profit?

\item How does equilibrium change with $n$ bidders?\end{enumerate}
